<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-04-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-04-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="91" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">741.65/536a</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to
                            the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-04-18">April 18, 1938</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>I have just read Halifax’s communication to Kennedy—and I suppose the last
                        paragraph needs some answer. Will you talk to me about this at your
                        convenience.</p>
                    <closer><signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps">oosevelt</hi>]</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>